HEADWORD: Cross-staff
<hw>Cross"-staff`</hw> <pr>(-st?f`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>An instrument formerly used at sea for taking the altitudes of
celestial bodies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A surveyor's instrument for measuring
offsets.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cross-stitch</ent>⟦br⟧
